1
00:01:47,307 --> 00:01:49,677
(Nirvana Sutra) Verse 19:

2
00:01:50,077 --> 00:01:53,417
"The worst of the Eight Hells
is called Continuous Hell."

3
00:01:53,947 --> 00:01:56,967
"It has the meaning of
Continuous Suffering. Thus the name."

4
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:33,095
I started this gang five years ago
on Tuen Mun island.

5
00:02:33,787 --> 00:02:37,537
Back then we were only selling hashish.

6
00:02:39,092 --> 00:02:42,462
We were full of ambition.

7
00:02:43,930 --> 00:02:46,620
But after only a couple of weeks,

8
00:02:47,067 --> 00:02:50,697
the cops started hunting us down.

9
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:55,460
Within one year,

10
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:58,770
six of our brothers died.

11
00:03:07,821 --> 00:03:09,901
But Buddha spared me!

12
00:03:17,731 --> 00:03:21,071
"What millions died
that Caesar might be great!"

13
00:03:22,536 --> 00:03:24,846
But I don't believe in destiny.

14
00:03:26,173 --> 00:03:31,443
We now have the power
to take fate in our own hands.

15
00:03:33,246 --> 00:03:36,236
You are the youngest brothers in my gang

16
00:03:37,284 --> 00:03:39,714
and you have clean records.

17
00:03:41,154 --> 00:03:44,614
You can be my eyes and ears
in the police force.

18
00:03:51,331 --> 00:03:53,171
OK.

19
00:03:54,835 --> 00:03:56,765
Just never forget...

20
00:03:57,971 --> 00:04:00,631
you're always working for me.

21
00:04:02,576 --> 00:04:04,626
Bottoms up, "officers."

22
00:04:21,862 --> 00:04:24,582
Cadet Yan, when you were debriefed
ten minutes ago,

23
00:04:25,031 --> 00:04:27,521
tell me, how many files were on my desk?

24
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:32,854
Six, sir. Four beige on the left,
two red ones on the right.

25
00:04:38,145 --> 00:04:41,075
Any observations about me?

26
00:04:41,548 --> 00:04:43,798
Sorry to point this out, but...

27
00:04:44,184 --> 00:04:47,084
you must have been in a hurry,
your socks don't match.

28
00:04:54,761 --> 00:04:57,921
- Cadet Yan, you're dismissed.
- Yes, sir.

29
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:05,510
You owe me $500.

30
00:05:07,207 --> 00:05:08,757
Here's a down payment.

31
00:05:09,042 --> 00:05:11,441
Yan will be the perfect undercover cop.

32
00:05:11,845 --> 00:05:14,245
(man) You're in cadet school now,
and you'll follow the rules.

33
00:05:14,648 --> 00:05:16,818
You break the rules
and you're out, like him.

34
00:05:17,184 --> 00:05:19,024
Expelled.

35
00:05:22,589 --> 00:05:25,199
Who wants to be like ex-cadet Yan?

36
00:05:36,203 --> 00:05:38,542
Ido.

37
00:05:43,043 --> 00:05:46,293
(cadet school principal) Officer Yan,
your mission is to infiltrate the Triads.

38
00:05:46,813 --> 00:05:48,652
Your records at the cadet school
no longer exist.

39
00:05:48,982 --> 00:05:51,532
Only Superintendent Wong and!
will know your true identity.

40
00:05:51,952 --> 00:05:55,612
This mission is highly dangerous.
Do you understand?

41
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:57,799
- Yes, sir.
- (siren)

42
00:05:58,091 --> 00:06:00,021
(Yan) This job is killing me.

43
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:04,004
I'm either harassed by cops
or beaten up by gangsters.

44
00:06:05,498 --> 00:06:07,748
Officer Lau. You're still a rookie.

45
00:06:08,134 --> 00:06:10,274
Why do you think
you should get the promotion?

46
00:06:11,504 --> 00:06:14,664
Just hang on?
How'd you like me to hang you?

47
00:06:16,443 --> 00:06:19,603
l was at the top of my class,
and I'm deeply committed.

48
00:06:20,113 --> 00:06:22,453
lam the best candidate for the job, sir.

49
00:06:41,668 --> 00:06:42,958
Let's go.

50
00:06:48,041 --> 00:06:50,761
Stand over there and say "cheese."

51
00:06:51,912 --> 00:06:55,042
YAN - UNDERCOVER COP

52
00:06:57,117 --> 00:07:00,137
LAU - GANG MOLE

53
00:07:05,292 --> 00:07:08,392
INFERNAL AFFAIRS

54
00:07:27,981 --> 00:07:29,681
- Hello?
- Yeah.

55
00:07:32,285 --> 00:07:36,035
- Can I try this stereo?
- With what speakers?

56
00:07:36,623 --> 00:07:39,522
I don't know. Any recommendations?

57
00:07:41,061 --> 00:07:44,960
Here's a great tube amp from Hong Kong,
only ten grand.

58
00:07:47,434 --> 00:07:50,974
And use this cheap cable. These sound
as good as expensive European amps.

59
00:07:51,538 --> 00:07:54,668
Sweet high notes, crisp middle, deep bass.

60
00:07:55,175 --> 00:07:57,545
In a word: excellent.

61
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:00,862
Here, take a seat.

62
00:08:02,248 --> 00:08:04,238
(f "Forgotten Time" by Tsai Chin)

63
00:08:07,787 --> 00:08:10,277
Let the sound take you away.

64
00:08:11,658 --> 00:08:13,738
Feel that?

65
00:08:15,028 --> 00:08:17,638
The voice drifts right through you.

66
00:08:30,744 --> 00:08:32,824
Try this cable.

67
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:35,808
It's even better. Trust me.

68
00:08:39,152 --> 00:08:41,142
(f "Forgotten Time" by Tsai Chin)

69
00:08:41,488 --> 00:08:44,268
- Well?
- Much better.

70
00:08:46,993 --> 00:08:49,893
Do I get a discount if buy the whole set?

71
00:08:50,363 --> 00:08:53,793
Buy the amp here, but not the speakers.

72
00:08:54,334 --> 00:08:56,613
They're cheaper at Cheung Wai's.

73
00:08:57,971 --> 00:09:01,041
- Who should I ask for?
- Just tell them Yan sent you.

74
00:09:08,081 --> 00:09:10,541
- Which one's mine?
- The middle copy.

75
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:13,560
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

76
00:09:13,987 --> 00:09:16,947
- ls Cheung Wai's open yet?
- Sure.

77
00:09:17,424 --> 00:09:20,233
You bastard. l asked you to watch
the store, not send customers away.

78
00:09:20,693 --> 00:09:22,533
Your speakers are overpriced.

79
00:09:22,862 --> 00:09:26,401
How else am I supposed to pay your boss
protection money?

80
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,810
You don't look poor to me.

81
00:09:29,936 --> 00:09:31,606
- Hey, the cable.
- I'll bring it back.

82
00:09:31,905 --> 00:09:33,925
I can't sell it after it's opened.

83
00:09:34,307 --> 00:09:37,027
- Where are you going?
- A funeral.

84
00:10:07,307 --> 00:10:09,357
Yan, you've been busted for assault
three times.

85
00:10:09,742 --> 00:10:13,432
So I'm officially setting you up
with a departmental shrink.

86
00:10:14,013 --> 00:10:16,233
You're much too involved with your role.

87
00:10:18,551 --> 00:10:22,861
You're acting like a real criminal.
Have you forgotten you're a cop?

88
00:10:25,525 --> 00:10:30,475
You told me it's only for three years.
But you extend it over and over.

89
00:10:33,733 --> 00:10:36,073
I've been doing this shit for ten years.

90
00:10:37,437 --> 00:10:39,487
You're the deepest agent we've got.

91
00:10:39,839 --> 00:10:42,009
I'm the only one left
who knows your real identity.

92
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:45,445
I could erase your file
if you'd rather be a gangster.

93
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:52,351
What do you want me to do?
Never get my hands dirty?

94
00:10:52,952 --> 00:10:57,402
That doesn't work for a gangster.
I might as well wear my badge!

95
00:11:02,862 --> 00:11:05,901
- When will Sam place his order?
- Who knows.

96
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:15,310
- Sometime this week.
- What?

97
00:11:15,608 --> 00:11:17,417
Sometime this week.

98
00:11:19,846 --> 00:11:24,706
The Thais are here. Once we get
the drugs, they'll be put in the warehouse.

99
00:11:26,386 --> 00:11:29,045
- Where is that?
- How the hell do I know?

100
00:11:29,489 --> 00:11:32,069
Sam won't tell me that stuff yet.

101
00:11:35,295 --> 00:11:39,834
- Yan, you can retire after this.
- Bullshit. I've heard that one before.

102
00:11:55,081 --> 00:11:56,631
Crap, these lousy mikes again?

103
00:11:56,916 --> 00:12:00,516
How am I supposed to conceal
this outdated piece of shit?

104
00:12:01,087 --> 00:12:03,516
You'll find a way to hide it.

105
00:12:03,923 --> 00:12:05,763
I'll stick it up my ass.

106
00:12:15,635 --> 00:12:18,064
What's this, a camera?

107
00:12:18,905 --> 00:12:21,074
How does it work?

108
00:12:21,441 --> 00:12:23,901
It's real. It's for your birthday.

109
00:12:26,879 --> 00:12:28,809
l hate watches.

110
00:13:01,748 --> 00:13:03,918
- You arrested them?
- Yes.

111
00:13:04,284 --> 00:13:08,234
But if we don't get something soon,
they'll have to be released.

112
00:13:08,855 --> 00:13:10,725
Tea time.

113
00:13:11,891 --> 00:13:14,471
- You want tea, boss?
- With milk, thanks.

114
00:13:14,894 --> 00:13:17,414
(woman) He's been stonewalling us.

115
00:13:17,830 --> 00:13:22,280
(man) We need to get something
before his attorney arrives.

116
00:13:52,398 --> 00:13:55,558
I'm not talking without my lawyer.

117
00:13:57,704 --> 00:14:00,723
lam your attorney.
Have you said anything?

118
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:07,318
Nothing at all.

119
00:14:08,381 --> 00:14:13,420
That's good. You should tell me now
if you mentioned any names.

120
00:14:15,154 --> 00:14:18,814
Brother Mo told me to ask you
if your family needs any help.

121
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:24,430
Don't get nervous. They can't record
anything while a lawyer is present.

122
00:14:37,043 --> 00:14:39,093
Brother Mo sent you?

123
00:14:41,914 --> 00:14:45,514
Those two kids next door
squealed on the hideout already.

124
00:14:46,119 --> 00:14:48,289
The cops are on their way.

125
00:14:48,688 --> 00:14:52,608
I know Brother Mo
told you not to say anything.

126
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:58,970
But he needs to be warned.
I don't know his emergency number.

127
00:14:59,665 --> 00:15:01,655
Here.

128
00:15:16,048 --> 00:15:18,268
- What now?
- That's it.

129
00:15:19,085 --> 00:15:22,485
It will set off an alarm. You better be right.

130
00:15:25,958 --> 00:15:27,887
OK. Don't worry.

131
00:15:29,562 --> 00:15:32,722
I'll see if l can bail you out.

132
00:15:34,567 --> 00:15:36,497
Take care.

133
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:42,399
Remember, don't talk to any of the police.

134
00:15:42,809 --> 00:15:45,029
I won't say a word.

135
00:15:47,113 --> 00:15:48,423
- Fanny!
- Yes?

136
00:15:48,681 --> 00:15:50,671
Here.

137
00:15:51,017 --> 00:15:52,217
- Track this number.
- Sure.

138
00:15:52,452 --> 00:15:54,732
This is Mo's hideout.

139
00:16:02,762 --> 00:16:04,311
711 Cheung Fai Road, second floor.

140
00:16:04,597 --> 00:16:09,167
To all cars: 711 Cheung Fai Road,
second floor. OK.

141
00:16:09,869 --> 00:16:10,889
(Fanny) Boss.

142
00:16:11,103 --> 00:16:13,563
- All set.
- Smart guy.

143
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:15,553
- Where's my tea?
- Here.

144
00:16:15,842 --> 00:16:17,682
Thanks.

145
00:16:19,078 --> 00:16:23,208
That was great.
l had no idea you were a lawyer.

146
00:16:25,518 --> 00:16:27,388
(phone rings)

147
00:16:29,222 --> 00:16:31,531
Thanks.

148
00:16:33,526 --> 00:16:35,835
Hello, yes.

149
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:39,459
Sure, no problem.

150
00:16:39,799 --> 00:16:43,429
Listen up. We're on another case.
Overtime tonight.

151
00:16:51,878 --> 00:16:53,928
(Wong) Our target is a major drug cartel.

152
00:16:55,147 --> 00:16:59,307
In one hour they'll be doing a deal
with a Thai seller.

153
00:17:00,386 --> 00:17:04,546
Cash will be handed over
in the building across the street.

154
00:17:08,594 --> 00:17:10,994
But the delivery location of the goods
is still unknown.

155
00:17:11,430 --> 00:17:15,680
CIB will tag the target and tap their phones.

156
00:17:16,335 --> 00:17:21,985
We won't take action until our mole
has identified the delivery location.

157
00:17:22,842 --> 00:17:25,212
Let's take a look at our targets.

158
00:17:28,314 --> 00:17:32,674
Our principal stars tonight
are Boss Sam, Yan and Del Piero.

159
00:17:38,024 --> 00:17:41,014
It's taken a long time to get close,
so we'd better nail them tonight.

160
00:17:41,494 --> 00:17:43,333
OK? Let's go.

161
00:18:00,246 --> 00:18:02,876
Sorry for the short notice.

162
00:18:03,316 --> 00:18:06,596
- But we're keeping a tight lid on this one.
- You think he has cops on his payroll?

163
00:18:07,119 --> 00:18:09,049
- He's always a step ahead.
- Hello, Mom?

164
00:18:09,388 --> 00:18:11,378
Pass the phone to Mom.

165
00:18:12,592 --> 00:18:14,672
I can't make it to dinner.

166
00:18:15,661 --> 00:18:19,581
Too bad. It's too late
to cancel with our Thai friends.

167
00:18:23,336 --> 00:18:26,766
- You're so relaxed.
- The calm before the storm and all that.

168
00:18:27,306 --> 00:18:29,146
Sorry.

169
00:18:55,101 --> 00:18:58,381
We're monitoring all the area's cell phones.

170
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:03,260
SP Wong.

171
00:19:03,643 --> 00:19:07,213
- SP Wong, which channel?
- 454870.

172
00:19:43,683 --> 00:19:46,203
Get ready. They're pulling up.

173
00:20:17,383 --> 00:20:19,573
Give me your cell phones.

174
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:27,154
You two, watch the car.

175
00:20:27,493 --> 00:20:29,243
Wait.

176
00:20:30,463 --> 00:20:32,013
Yan.

177
00:20:32,298 --> 00:20:34,638
Bring the Thais in here.

178
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:37,407
You two, follow me.

179
00:20:37,837 --> 00:20:38,687
(phone beeps)

180
00:20:44,877 --> 00:20:46,307
- Lau.
- Yes.

181
00:20:46,579 --> 00:20:50,499
- Did Sam's gang make any calls?
- No. They probably changed phones.

182
00:20:51,117 --> 00:20:53,307
Let's scan for any calls
made from this area.

183
00:20:54,053 --> 00:20:56,303
Scanning.

184
00:20:56,689 --> 00:20:58,939
6,500 cell phones are active
in this area right now.

185
00:20:59,325 --> 00:21:02,755
267 cell phones are making calls
on this street alone.

186
00:21:03,295 --> 00:21:04,755
Give me a minute.

187
00:21:05,030 --> 00:21:07,580
- Good work.
- Thank you.

188
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:14,230
(Fanny, speaking through fixed smile)
They're looking this way.

189
00:21:14,774 --> 00:21:17,704
Are those two watching us?

190
00:21:18,177 --> 00:21:20,986
- Which two?
- Those two.

191
00:21:23,249 --> 00:21:27,909
- No one's watching us.
- Those two making out over there.

192
00:21:28,621 --> 00:21:31,811
They're making out.
You think they'd rather watch you?

193
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:37,907
- Watch the door.
- Yep, we see him.

194
00:21:49,975 --> 00:21:51,784
Boss. They're here.

195
00:21:52,111 --> 00:21:53,541
(Sam) Hey, man!

196
00:21:53,813 --> 00:21:56,423
- What's up?
- How are you?

197
00:21:56,849 --> 00:21:58,928
Cigar?

198
00:22:00,653 --> 00:22:02,643
Any good?

199
00:22:02,988 --> 00:22:05,038
The best.

200
00:22:10,763 --> 00:22:13,193
- You like our weather?
- Very cold.

201
00:22:13,599 --> 00:22:15,739
I knew you'd say that!

202
00:22:17,336 --> 00:22:18,536
(Sam laughs)

203
00:22:18,771 --> 00:22:21,261
Thais can't take the cold.

204
00:22:21,674 --> 00:22:23,664
This is nothing.

205
00:22:51,170 --> 00:22:53,720
A-1.

206
00:22:56,842 --> 00:22:59,272
You got a deal!

207
00:23:03,549 --> 00:23:05,859
(phone rings)

208
00:23:09,588 --> 00:23:12,578
License plate number HN397 is taking off.

209
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:17,308
Repeat. Helen Nelson 397 is taking off.

210
00:23:22,902 --> 00:23:25,042
Should we tail them?

211
00:23:36,715 --> 00:23:38,995
Elephant, follow car number one.

212
00:23:39,385 --> 00:23:41,725
Roger. Follow him.

213
00:23:47,559 --> 00:23:50,399
Piero, you're being tailed.
Lead them in circles.

214
00:24:01,307 --> 00:24:03,297
They know our channel.

215
00:24:03,642 --> 00:24:06,132
Switch to a new one.

216
00:24:12,017 --> 00:24:14,327
Sam, what's going on?

217
00:24:15,988 --> 00:24:18,828
Don't worry. Take it easy.

218
00:24:28,434 --> 00:24:30,624
Take care of the Thais for me.

219
00:24:41,814 --> 00:24:43,334
(phone rings)

220
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:47,701
Excuse me.

221
00:24:53,025 --> 00:24:54,755
Yes?

222
00:24:55,060 --> 00:24:57,280
Use the walkie-talkies.
We switched channels.

223
00:24:57,663 --> 00:24:59,003
Are you finished?

224
00:24:59,264 --> 00:25:01,724
- 45...
- Shut up!

225
00:25:05,437 --> 00:25:08,367
Piero, are you being tailed?

226
00:25:09,775 --> 00:25:11,705
Keep circling.

227
00:25:34,900 --> 00:25:36,300
Cheung.

228
00:25:36,568 --> 00:25:39,258
Use the old channel to tell them
we're aborting the mission.

229
00:25:39,705 --> 00:25:41,225
Yes, sir.

230
00:25:44,476 --> 00:25:47,906
Elephant, abort. Return to the station.

231
00:25:48,447 --> 00:25:50,637
(man) Roger.

232
00:25:57,389 --> 00:25:58,089
All clear.

233
00:25:58,257 --> 00:26:01,767
What's going on?
Our guys are freezing out there.

234
00:26:04,596 --> 00:26:06,326
What's so funny?

235
00:26:06,632 --> 00:26:09,412
l speak Thai. l know what they're saying.

236
00:26:09,868 --> 00:26:10,628
Oh, yeah?

237
00:26:10,803 --> 00:26:15,403
Yeah. They're complaining
about their jobs.

238
00:26:16,108 --> 00:26:17,447
What exactly?

239
00:26:17,709 --> 00:26:21,139
Their guys at Lung Koo Ray
are freezing to death.

240
00:26:21,680 --> 00:26:24,610
They think this is cold.

241
00:26:26,085 --> 00:26:29,515
That's right. You're sharp.

242
00:26:47,306 --> 00:26:49,646
(whispering)

243
00:26:54,146 --> 00:26:56,286
(amplified tapping)

244
00:27:02,187 --> 00:27:04,617
Cheung, order all cars to Lung Koo Ray.

245
00:27:20,672 --> 00:27:22,042
Boss, I see them.

246
00:27:22,307 --> 00:27:26,057
Tell Keung to check the goods.
And make sure no one is around.

247
00:27:27,546 --> 00:27:29,626
Not a soul.

248
00:27:34,887 --> 00:27:38,137
(over radio) Sam's men are here.
They're checking the goods.

249
00:27:44,763 --> 00:27:47,312
Yo, the coke is all here!

250
00:27:47,733 --> 00:27:49,812
Don't be an idiot.

251
00:27:50,169 --> 00:27:52,449
- Boss.
- [heard.

252
00:27:52,838 --> 00:27:55,268
Tell Keung to shout out
that the cocaine is his.

253
00:27:56,475 --> 00:28:00,695
Keung, the Boss wants you
to shout out the cocaine is yours.

254
00:28:02,281 --> 00:28:04,801
The cocaine is yours.

255
