267
00:29:11,483 --> 00:29:13,473
(dials)

268
00:29:16,054 --> 00:29:18,604
- (Sam) Throw it overboard! Now!
- (sirens)

269
00:29:19,458 --> 00:29:20,858
Keung, ditch the shit!

270
00:29:21,159 --> 00:29:22,179
Police. Freeze.

271
00:29:22,427 --> 00:29:24,506
(shouting and confusion over the radio)

272
00:29:28,233 --> 00:29:30,013
Hurry! Toss it!

273
00:29:31,803 --> 00:29:33,993
Go! Go!

274
00:29:34,806 --> 00:29:36,326
Dump it all!

275
00:29:36,608 --> 00:29:38,568
We got the men, but lost the goods.
It's all in the water.

276
00:29:38,910 --> 00:29:40,930
Team seven, hold it. Hold it.

277
00:29:57,929 --> 00:29:59,739
Everyone, follow me.

278
00:30:00,098 --> 00:30:02,028
3G
What are you looking at?

279
00:30:34,166 --> 00:30:36,186
Boss, let's...

280
00:30:57,322 --> 00:30:59,462
Police. Police. Don't move.

281
00:31:45,470 --> 00:31:47,460
Sam.

282
00:31:47,806 --> 00:31:50,646
- That looks good.
- Not bad.

283
00:31:52,043 --> 00:31:55,003
Seems you were right.
Your boys were only strolling on the beach.

284
00:31:55,847 --> 00:31:58,067
- So they can go now?
- Sure, anytime.

285
00:31:58,450 --> 00:32:01,320
Or they can join you here for supper.

286
00:32:01,787 --> 00:32:05,297
You haven't had us over for some time.
I'm surprised it's not poisoned.

287
00:32:05,857 --> 00:32:08,077
There's always dessert, you know.

288
00:32:09,995 --> 00:32:13,774
I'll pass. But I feel bad
that you prepared all this for nothing.

289
00:32:14,366 --> 00:32:19,196
And I feel bad that this meal cost you
people a couple hundred grand tonight.

290
00:32:41,426 --> 00:32:43,826
You think planting a mole
will take us down?

291
00:32:44,229 --> 00:32:46,419
You think so too.

292
00:33:04,316 --> 00:33:06,776
There's an old story.

293
00:33:07,185 --> 00:33:09,205
Two guys need kidney transplants,

294
00:33:09,554 --> 00:33:11,424
but only one is available.

295
00:33:11,756 --> 00:33:14,066
So they play a game.

296
00:33:14,459 --> 00:33:16,449
They each put a playing card
into the other's pocket.

297
00:33:16,795 --> 00:33:20,455
Whoever guesses
the card in his own pocket wins.

298
00:33:22,834 --> 00:33:25,384
You know I can see your card.

299
00:33:26,738 --> 00:33:29,078
I know yours too.

300
00:33:32,978 --> 00:33:35,588
- I'll beat you.
- We'll see.

301
00:33:36,948 --> 00:33:39,608
- Well, we'll be more careful.
- Me too.

302
00:33:40,886 --> 00:33:42,726
I'm sure you realize,

303
00:33:43,054 --> 00:33:45,394
the game's loser dies.

304
00:33:47,125 --> 00:33:49,645
Then you're dead already.

305
00:33:54,232 --> 00:33:57,252
Ever seen someone
shake a corpse's hand?

306
00:34:01,072 --> 00:34:02,911
Let's go.

307
00:34:23,027 --> 00:34:25,107
Next to the couch.

308
00:34:29,900 --> 00:34:31,190
- Mary?
- What?

309
00:34:31,436 --> 00:34:36,446
- What's the decorator's number?
- The interior designer? 9025 5047.

310
00:34:38,109 --> 00:34:41,478
Now I lost count. Where was I?

311
00:34:42,047 --> 00:34:43,357
24.

312
00:34:43,614 --> 00:34:46,834
- 24? Are you sure?
- Positive.

313
00:34:49,120 --> 00:34:51,290
- Give me the phone.
- Coming.

314
00:34:52,524 --> 00:34:54,774
(phone rings)

315
00:34:56,094 --> 00:34:57,764
Hello?

316
00:34:58,063 --> 00:35:00,313
Who is it?

317
00:35:00,699 --> 00:35:02,629
- Hello?
- It's me.

318
00:35:02,968 --> 00:35:07,308
Hi. I'm moving in.
Don't eavesdrop. It's police business.

319
00:35:07,973 --> 00:35:09,783
I lost my goods.

320
00:35:10,976 --> 00:35:13,996
- Find me this mole.
- Hold on, I'll go outside.

321
00:35:16,381 --> 00:35:19,951
- [ don't have access to undercover files.
- [ don't care how difficult it is.

322
00:35:22,854 --> 00:35:25,634
l only know he uses Morse code.

323
00:35:29,861 --> 00:35:35,051
Give me all the information
on your people from last night.

324
00:35:35,834 --> 00:35:40,283
Their real names, ID numbers,
bank accounts, et cetera.

325
00:35:40,972 --> 00:35:44,432
- Bring it to the theater tonight.
- OK.

326
00:35:49,481 --> 00:35:51,971
What's up?

327
00:35:53,985 --> 00:35:55,445
It's 29.

328
00:35:56,755 --> 00:35:59,125
- 28
- 29.

329
00:35:59,524 --> 00:36:03,304
Not the boxes.
I know what my next novel will be about.

330
00:36:04,829 --> 00:36:08,699
- Aman with 28 personalities.
- Your mother?

331
00:36:09,300 --> 00:36:10,910
- Don't joke.
- I'll stop.

332
00:36:11,202 --> 00:36:14,012
Think about it. A man with 28 personalities.

333
00:36:14,472 --> 00:36:17,082
The second he wakes up,
he could be anybody.

334
00:36:17,542 --> 00:36:19,712
He starts to forget which one
is the real him.

335
00:36:21,513 --> 00:36:23,212
- Creepy, right?
- Very creepy.

336
00:36:23,515 --> 00:36:26,004
- You like it?
- Yeah, a bestseller, for sure.

337
00:36:26,451 --> 00:36:27,531
- Hold on.
- What?

338
00:36:27,752 --> 00:36:30,122
- Why's the chair so big?
- Which one?

339
00:36:31,022 --> 00:36:33,712
I must have messed up the measurements.

340
00:36:34,159 --> 00:36:35,529
(she groans)

341
00:36:35,794 --> 00:36:38,314
Take it easy. You get so carried away.

342
00:36:38,730 --> 00:36:41,450
Let's see. Maybe we can make it fit.

343
00:36:41,900 --> 00:36:43,770
Relax.

344
00:36:49,674 --> 00:36:51,724
(Yan) Meet up? You want me dead?

345
00:36:52,077 --> 00:36:55,677
One of your officers is a mole.
Find him, then we'll meet.

346
00:36:57,148 --> 00:36:59,368
I can't help you.

347
00:36:59,784 --> 00:37:01,974
It's impossible.

348
00:37:02,353 --> 00:37:04,523
What? Later.

349
00:37:04,889 --> 00:37:07,109
I just can't talk right now.

350
00:37:07,492 --> 00:37:09,392
l have an appointment.

351
00:37:09,728 --> 00:37:12,418
I'm seeing your damn shrink!

352
00:37:14,399 --> 00:37:16,679
(clock ticks)

353
00:37:38,490 --> 00:37:40,390
(alarm beeps)

354
00:38:10,288 --> 00:38:13,188
This chair is... incredible.

355
00:38:14,626 --> 00:38:15,826
I'll tell you where you can get one.

356
00:38:16,060 --> 00:38:17,640
So you don't have to waste your time
coming here.

357
00:38:17,929 --> 00:38:19,479
It's more comfortable here.

358
00:38:20,899 --> 00:38:22,098
Don't be so mean.

359
00:38:22,500 --> 00:38:25,130
If it weren't for me,
for the past four months...

360
00:38:25,570 --> 00:38:27,150
You'd have no time to play video games.

361
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:30,500
It's been five months.

362
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:34,150
Pretty soon your mandatory "therapy"
will end.

363
00:38:34,479 --> 00:38:36,319
Then you can sleep at home.

364
00:38:37,682 --> 00:38:38,942
So soon?

365
00:38:40,685 --> 00:38:42,585
You don't see any improvements?

366
00:38:43,288 --> 00:38:45,808
Can't you prolong my treatment?

367
00:38:46,457 --> 00:38:51,287
I've started getting migraines.
Might be schizophrenia.

368
00:38:52,964 --> 00:38:55,574
Therapy doesn't cure headaches.
I'll prescribe some aspirin.

369
00:38:59,637 --> 00:39:02,417
Actually, l do want to ask you something.

370
00:39:02,874 --> 00:39:05,394
It's kind of embarrassing.

371
00:39:05,810 --> 00:39:08,150
What do you think of me?

372
00:39:12,617 --> 00:39:14,837
Do you think I'm a good guy or a bad guy?

373
00:39:16,921 --> 00:39:19,231
l hardly know you at all.

374
00:39:26,264 --> 00:39:29,774
If l tell you something,
will you keep it a secret?

375
00:39:33,838 --> 00:39:36,238
I'm a cop.

376
00:39:40,745 --> 00:39:43,115
Soaml.

377
00:39:50,054 --> 00:39:52,634
OK, I'll see you next week.
Try to remember your dreams.

378
00:39:54,192 --> 00:39:55,942
Of course.

379
00:39:56,294 --> 00:39:58,694
I'll dream of you.

380
00:39:59,097 --> 00:40:01,147
See you next week.

381
00:40:04,435 --> 00:40:06,424
Just aspirin, that's all?

382
00:40:11,542 --> 00:40:13,382
Bye-bye.

383
00:40:18,149 --> 00:40:20,929
You're going to get promoted.

384
00:40:21,386 --> 00:40:25,836
You'll work for Internal Affairs,
but you'll stay at OCTB.

385
00:40:27,492 --> 00:40:29,712
Why?

386
00:40:30,128 --> 00:40:32,818
Sam has a mole in the department.

387
00:40:33,264 --> 00:40:35,954
- want you to find him.
- Why me?

388
00:40:37,001 --> 00:40:39,931
We've vetted all candidates.

389
00:40:40,405 --> 00:40:43,745
You have an immaculate record.
You did a great job at CIB.

390
00:40:45,243 --> 00:40:48,643
Working in IA puts you in touch
with senior officials.

391
00:40:49,180 --> 00:40:51,399
It's a great opportunity.

392
00:40:51,783 --> 00:40:54,563
I can already tell

393
00:40:55,019 --> 00:40:57,629
you're going to be a great addition.

394
00:40:59,924 --> 00:41:03,384
- When will l meet the Board?
- lam the Board.

395
00:41:03,962 --> 00:41:06,952
Come on, take a swing.

396
00:41:11,803 --> 00:41:13,353
Thanks.

397
00:41:13,638 --> 00:41:17,508
By the way, how's the wedding coming?

398
00:41:18,109 --> 00:41:19,949
Everything's on schedule.

399
00:41:20,278 --> 00:41:24,227
That's great.
Marriage will improve your stability.

400
00:41:24,849 --> 00:41:26,719
As well as your image.

401
00:41:27,051 --> 00:41:29,741
You'll get promoted faster.

402
00:41:31,322 --> 00:41:34,602
Time to broaden your horizons.

403
00:41:36,928 --> 00:41:38,268
(Keung) Use your real name.

404
00:41:38,563 --> 00:41:41,753
That is my real name.
You know my name is Del Piero.

405
00:41:42,300 --> 00:41:44,610
Really?

406
00:41:52,043 --> 00:41:54,093
What's going on?

407
00:41:54,445 --> 00:41:57,405
The Boss told us to fill out these forms.

408
00:41:57,882 --> 00:42:02,392
Must be setting up mutual provident funds
for us. You know, MPF.

409
00:42:04,956 --> 00:42:07,206
You don't know how to spell "bodyguard"?

410
00:42:07,592 --> 00:42:10,692
- What, this isn't right?
- Not even close.

411
00:42:23,541 --> 00:42:26,701
- That's how you spell it.
- All right, professor.

412
00:42:27,211 --> 00:42:29,401
(woman's singing)

413
00:42:52,503 --> 00:42:54,843
I'm getting a shipment in.

414
00:42:55,239 --> 00:42:57,079
They're watching.

415
00:42:57,408 --> 00:42:59,518
Do what you need to do.

416
00:42:59,877 --> 00:43:01,866
But get this mole.

417
00:43:03,147 --> 00:43:05,636
I don't have access.
I can't arouse suspicion.

418
00:43:06,050 --> 00:43:08,680
So you're not worried about me,

419
00:43:09,120 --> 00:43:11,990
you're worried about yourself,
Inspector Lau.

420
00:43:15,493 --> 00:43:17,633
God, these girls are ugly.

421
00:43:27,872 --> 00:43:30,042
I'll take care of it.

422
00:44:25,029 --> 00:44:26,579
(phone rings)

423
00:44:32,403 --> 00:44:34,272
Hello?

424
00:44:36,974 --> 00:44:38,844
I'm coming.

425
00:45:22,253 --> 00:45:24,093
Yan.

426
00:45:25,423 --> 00:45:28,823
- How long have you been with me?
- Over three years.

427
00:45:29,360 --> 00:45:32,400
That long? Time flies.

428
00:45:35,833 --> 00:45:37,673
l have another shipment next week.

429
00:45:38,002 --> 00:45:42,252
But this time, I'm using some new faces.

430
00:45:42,907 --> 00:45:45,047
You guys can rest.

431
00:45:47,912 --> 00:45:50,462
- Even Keung?
- Keung?

432
00:45:54,085 --> 00:45:56,745
He's nuts, you know.

433
00:46:08,633 --> 00:46:11,062
So you've heard about this cop mole?

434
00:46:17,375 --> 00:46:19,925
What should we do?

435
00:46:20,344 --> 00:46:23,094
- I'll take care of it.
- You will?

436
00:46:35,459 --> 00:46:38,999
I'll find out who he is in a couple of days.
Be ready.

437
00:46:41,465 --> 00:46:43,305
Yan.

438
00:46:45,736 --> 00:46:48,136
I trust you the most of all.

439
00:47:12,163 --> 00:47:14,713
(Wong) Lau, come here.

440
00:47:22,273 --> 00:47:24,083
No, thanks.

441
00:47:28,479 --> 00:47:32,379
- Pretty tense.
- Just think of them as old friends.

442
00:47:33,017 --> 00:47:36,477
They're not so friendly right now.

443
00:47:38,889 --> 00:47:41,349
They know you're here to dig out the mole.

444
00:47:41,759 --> 00:47:44,249
What do you want from them,
a standing ovation?

445
00:47:44,662 --> 00:47:47,292
They're all under the microscope.

446
00:47:47,732 --> 00:47:50,282
They want it to be over more than we do.

447
00:47:50,701 --> 00:47:52,341
Just tell me who's first on the list.

448
00:47:52,636 --> 00:47:55,036
OK. Any clues?

449
00:47:57,908 --> 00:48:01,098
Two days ago my guy
almost caught the mole.

450
00:48:01,645 --> 00:48:05,775
He lost him. But when Sam gets another
shipment, he'll have to make contact again.

451
00:48:06,450 --> 00:48:09,169
Stay on Sam and we'll find the mole.

452
00:48:10,254 --> 00:48:13,094
- Why do they need me?
- Don't say that.

453
00:48:13,557 --> 00:48:15,807
Division sent you because
they have confidence in you.

454
00:48:16,193 --> 00:48:17,923
Not everyone can handle IA cases.

455
00:48:18,229 --> 00:48:20,569
It's stuffy in here. Let's get some air.

456
00:48:20,965 --> 00:48:23,895
You want coffee? I'll pour you a cup.

457
00:48:28,873 --> 00:48:30,483
(types)

458
00:48:49,193 --> 00:48:52,973
Two days ago,
my guy almost caught the mole.

459
00:48:53,564 --> 00:48:56,754
Stay on Sam and we'll find the mole.

