00:49:46,016 --> 00:49:47,826
MORSE CODE

463
00:49:58,996 --> 00:50:01,986
CALL ME WHEN BED ARRIVES.
DO YOU MISS ME? SEE YOU LATER.

464
00:50:02,466 --> 00:50:06,806
- Yes?
- (Lau) The bed has arrived.

465
00:50:07,471 --> 00:50:09,781
Is that so? Comfortable?

466
00:50:10,174 --> 00:50:13,304
- You want to try it out?
- [have work to do.

467
00:50:15,279 --> 00:50:18,209
All work and no play...

468
00:50:18,682 --> 00:50:20,962
- No, I can't.
- Come on.

469
00:50:21,385 --> 00:50:24,225
How about next Saturday? I'm free then.

470
00:50:24,722 --> 00:50:27,792
OK. It's up to you.

471
00:50:33,063 --> 00:50:35,143
- Up already?
- Yes.

472
00:50:36,433 --> 00:50:39,243
We just "tested" the bed
and you're back at work?

473
00:50:39,703 --> 00:50:42,103
I'm very hardworking.

474
00:50:42,506 --> 00:50:45,375
- What are you writing now?
- Here.

475
00:50:46,777 --> 00:50:49,817
I'm getting worried. My main character
is turning out to be pathetic.

476
00:50:50,314 --> 00:50:52,424
Pathetic?

477
00:50:52,783 --> 00:50:57,703
He needs to be happier.
Maybe I should turn him into a good guy.

478
00:50:59,423 --> 00:51:03,343
I mean, he's good, but he does bad things.
How does something like that end?

479
00:51:04,395 --> 00:51:09,315
Good question. I'll leave it up to the genius.

480
00:51:10,067 --> 00:51:13,547
- Come back to bed.
- Help me with the ending.

481
00:51:14,104 --> 00:51:17,674
- lL can't.
- Then go back to sleep, old man.

482
00:51:30,287 --> 00:51:32,156
(dials)

483
00:51:35,025 --> 00:51:38,275
From now on you follow SP Wong
around the clock.

484
00:51:41,699 --> 00:51:47,299
- [know how to spot an undercover cop.
- How?

485
00:51:48,138 --> 00:51:52,208
If he's watching you,
but pretending to do something else,

486
00:51:52,843 --> 00:51:55,393
then he's a cop.

487
00:52:14,365 --> 00:52:16,674
Is that so?

488
00:52:17,067 --> 00:52:19,117
- Then everybody's a cop.
- They're everywhere.

489
00:52:22,873 --> 00:52:24,833
(men talking)

490
00:52:29,313 --> 00:52:30,833
Yan.

491
00:52:31,115 --> 00:52:32,924
Boss.

492
00:52:46,730 --> 00:52:48,840
- Watching something?
- You're a cop.

493
00:52:49,199 --> 00:52:49,869
Huh?

494
00:52:50,034 --> 00:52:52,314
We're playing "find the cop."

495
00:52:53,637 --> 00:52:55,887
Good luck.

496
00:52:56,774 --> 00:52:59,324
- I'm going for a massage. Wanna come?
- Forget it.

497
00:52:59,743 --> 00:53:01,583
Don't tell.

498
00:53:02,813 --> 00:53:04,863
- You're a cop.
- Shut up.

499
00:53:12,156 --> 00:53:16,136
- What a coincidence.
- Just shopping in the old neighborhood.

500
00:53:16,794 --> 00:53:18,844
Haven't seen you for ages.

501
00:53:19,196 --> 00:53:21,306
Almost seven years.

502
00:53:23,434 --> 00:53:26,834
- How are you?
- Married. And you?

503
00:53:27,771 --> 00:53:30,811
Still doing the same...?

504
00:53:36,280 --> 00:53:38,060
Mommy.

505
00:53:40,651 --> 00:53:43,020
- Your daughter?
- Yes.

506
00:53:44,922 --> 00:53:47,032
- How old is she?
- She's five.

507
00:53:48,258 --> 00:53:50,868
I've got to meet my husband, so...

508
00:53:52,730 --> 00:53:54,480
I'll see you around.

509
00:53:54,832 --> 00:53:57,412
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

510
00:54:00,404 --> 00:54:02,714
Mommy. I'm six!

511
00:54:03,107 --> 00:54:05,627
Sorry, Mommy always forgets.

512
00:54:41,111 --> 00:54:43,801
- Where are you now?
- On my way.

513
00:54:47,618 --> 00:54:49,638
(phone rings)

514
00:54:52,289 --> 00:54:56,299
- Hello?
- Boss, he's taking the subway.

515
00:54:58,896 --> 00:55:00,976
Keep on him.

516
00:55:18,315 --> 00:55:20,215
(dials)

517
00:55:23,320 --> 00:55:25,510
Boss, he's gone to the 24th floor.

518
00:55:25,889 --> 00:55:28,289
Don't move until I tell you.

519
00:55:40,003 --> 00:55:41,263
(dials)

520
00:55:43,941 --> 00:55:46,250
Boss, we've got him.

521
00:55:47,878 --> 00:55:50,628
Don't know yet.
But I know where he is now.

522
00:55:57,554 --> 00:55:59,604
Keep watch over here.

523
00:56:16,273 --> 00:56:17,583
(Wong) What's the word, Yan?

524
00:56:17,875 --> 00:56:20,715
A shipment's coming in next week.
Time and location still unknown.

525
00:56:21,178 --> 00:56:25,958
I don't know who Sam's mole is,
but he's confident he can find me.

526
00:56:27,618 --> 00:56:29,458
In that case...

527
00:56:35,058 --> 00:56:38,688
- We'd better get out.
- Are you kidding?

528
00:56:39,263 --> 00:56:41,982
I don't want you getting killed.

529
00:56:42,432 --> 00:56:43,721
(phone rings)

530
00:56:44,001 --> 00:56:45,811
Hello?

531
00:56:47,104 --> 00:56:50,473
Boss said he found the mole.
He told us to take care of him.

532
00:56:52,743 --> 00:56:54,613
I'll be right there.

533
00:57:11,895 --> 00:57:13,475
(phone rings)

534
00:57:14,164 --> 00:57:17,444
Hello? Find SP Wong!

535
00:57:32,783 --> 00:57:35,272
You two, take the stairs.

536
00:57:35,686 --> 00:57:37,586
Keung, take the elevator.

537
00:57:38,488 --> 00:57:40,627
- (Yan) Anyone know about our meeting?
- No.

538
00:57:40,991 --> 00:57:43,511
Sam's men are downstairs.

539
00:58:08,418 --> 00:58:09,678
(gun being cocked)

540
00:58:09,920 --> 00:58:13,320
Hey, what are you doing? Put it away.

541
00:58:23,600 --> 00:58:25,790
(footsteps)

542
00:58:39,216 --> 00:58:41,556
- Take the window-washing crane.
- What about you?

543
00:58:41,952 --> 00:58:44,292
I'll take the elevator. (taps gun)

544
00:58:45,355 --> 00:58:47,605
Be careful.

545
00:58:47,991 --> 00:58:50,271
Yan.

546
00:58:50,660 --> 00:58:52,500
Nothing.

547
00:59:20,590 --> 00:59:21,900
(dials)

548
00:59:26,997 --> 00:59:29,337
(ting)

549
00:59:30,534 --> 00:59:33,084
Darling, the apartment is superb.

550
00:59:33,503 --> 00:59:36,083
A 180-degree window
facing the golf course.

551
00:59:36,506 --> 00:59:38,846
Plus club membership and...

552
00:59:44,981 --> 00:59:47,411
Superintendent Wong.

553
00:59:56,660 --> 00:59:59,180
Drive around to the main entrance.

554
01:00:28,959 --> 01:00:31,269
(musical interlude)

555
01:00:51,348 --> 01:00:54,038
Any observations about me?

556
01:00:59,556 --> 01:01:02,246
It's real, It's for your birthday.

557
01:01:22,646 --> 01:01:24,986
Let's go. Police! Let's go!

558
01:01:56,479 --> 01:01:58,788
Boss. SP Wong is down!

559
01:02:50,967 --> 01:02:53,367
(newsreader) Shots rang out
in Sheung Wan this afternoon,

560
01:02:53,770 --> 01:02:57,460
leaving three people dead
and several others wounded.

561
01:02:58,041 --> 01:03:02,991
Police confirmed one of the dead
was OCTB Superintendent Wong.

562
01:03:03,747 --> 01:03:06,736
Details are sketchy, but it appears to be
a case of gang warfare.

563
01:03:07,217 --> 01:03:10,087
Triads in southern Kowloon
are suspected.

564
01:03:10,553 --> 01:03:14,183
The police chief
expressed his condolences

565
01:03:14,791 --> 01:03:17,451
and pledged to swiftly solve the case.

566
01:03:18,395 --> 01:03:20,205
(Keung) That was a close one.

567
01:03:20,597 --> 01:03:23,727
Ten minutes after you left,
Boss told us to get ready.

568
01:03:25,502 --> 01:03:30,282
l was scared shitless.
You know, I can't stand violence.

569
01:03:32,642 --> 01:03:34,752
But this was serious stuff.

570
01:03:35,111 --> 01:03:38,151
I just wanted to run away.

571
01:03:42,285 --> 01:03:46,325
Two days ago, Boss invited me
into his room.

572
01:03:46,990 --> 01:03:49,129
He asked me how long I'd worked for him.

573
01:03:49,492 --> 01:03:52,102
I couldn't even remember.

574
01:03:52,529 --> 01:03:57,719
So he says, "Keung,
it's been five years already."

575
01:03:58,501 --> 01:04:01,601
"And you've always been loyal."

576
01:04:02,105 --> 01:04:04,825
"l have a question for you."

577
01:04:05,275 --> 01:04:09,725
"If one of our brothers is a mole,
would you be able to take him out?"

578
01:04:10,413 --> 01:04:14,223
Of course I said "yes" to his face.
I'm no idiot!

579
01:04:16,353 --> 01:04:18,023
(coughs)

580
01:04:18,321 --> 01:04:22,221
It's just as well no one found the mole.

581
01:04:24,494 --> 01:04:26,714
That Wong guy was tough.

582
01:04:27,130 --> 01:04:31,580
They dragged him upstairs
and beat him for ten minutes.

583
01:04:32,268 --> 01:04:34,108
Ten long minutes.

584
01:04:37,741 --> 01:04:40,291
Ten long minutes.

585
01:04:40,710 --> 01:04:43,020
He didn't make a peep.

586
01:04:46,049 --> 01:04:47,979
(horn blares)

587
01:04:49,152 --> 01:04:50,992
Keung.

588
01:04:52,522 --> 01:04:57,092
Boss said the cops were hot on his trail.

589
01:05:00,663 --> 01:05:03,243
And whoever didn't show up today
is the mole.

590
01:05:04,868 --> 01:05:08,298
I didn't tell him you went for a massage.

591
01:05:09,773 --> 01:05:13,283
If he knew, you'd be dead.

592
01:05:15,945 --> 01:05:18,845
Yan, I want to ask you something.

593
01:05:19,315 --> 01:05:22,035
Is your masseuse pretty?

594
01:05:23,753 --> 01:05:25,273
Because...

595
01:05:26,556 --> 01:05:29,576
if she's a pig, it's not worth it.

596
01:05:31,194 --> 01:05:32,564
(coughs)

597
01:05:34,564 --> 01:05:36,783
Get out of here.

598
01:05:37,200 --> 01:05:40,540
Cops'll be here any minute.

599
01:05:43,339 --> 01:05:45,739
Remember this.

600
01:05:48,077 --> 01:05:50,067
If you see someone watching you,

601
01:05:51,514 --> 01:05:54,124
but pretending...

602
01:05:54,551 --> 01:05:56,891
to do something else,

603
01:05:59,756 --> 01:06:00,926
they're a cop.

604
01:06:02,091 --> 01:06:04,611
(Keung stops breathing)

605
01:06:20,376 --> 01:06:22,486
(horn blares)

606
01:06:46,636 --> 01:06:50,416
(man) Closed circuit TV shows us
SP Wong entered the building at 4:15pm.

607
01:06:50,974 --> 01:06:53,584
The suspects entered 20 minutes later.

608
01:06:55,011 --> 01:06:58,381
At 4:38pm
we received Inspector Lau's report.

609
01:07:00,617 --> 01:07:04,397
Eight minutes before we arrived,
a body fell off the building.

610
01:07:05,822 --> 01:07:07,372
It was SP Wong.

611
01:07:07,657 --> 01:07:11,607
All the suspects killed or injured
belong to Sam's gang.

612
01:07:12,228 --> 01:07:15,688
Many others got away.

613
01:07:16,266 --> 01:07:19,286
Do you know why
SP Wong went to that building?

614
01:07:23,039 --> 01:07:25,849
Not sure. I had CIB following him.

615
01:07:26,309 --> 01:07:28,329
Why was CIB following him?

616
01:07:28,678 --> 01:07:30,698
That's IA's business.

617
01:07:31,047 --> 01:07:33,707
Now that SP Wong is dead,
it is OCTB's business.

618
01:07:34,150 --> 01:07:35,320
What kind of attitude is that?

619
01:07:35,552 --> 01:07:37,802
SP Wong was a loyal man
and you investigated him?

620
01:07:38,187 --> 01:07:41,057
- What kind of attitude is that?
- You have to let us do our jobs.

621
01:07:41,524 --> 01:07:44,214
You screwed up
or SP Wong wouldn't be dead.

622
01:07:44,661 --> 01:07:47,001
- I'm talking business here.
- And I'm getting personal.

623
01:07:47,397 --> 01:07:49,386
Nobody wanted this, OK?

624
01:07:55,238 --> 01:07:56,578
Sorry, sir.

625
01:07:58,808 --> 01:08:00,828
It was my negligence.

626
01:08:02,645 --> 01:08:05,425
I'm just as angry as you. Sorry.

627
01:08:10,920 --> 01:08:14,820
SP Wong has a file
on our undercover officer in Sam's gang.

628
01:08:15,425 --> 01:08:19,785
But it's locked with a password.
The technical staff can't open it.

629
01:08:20,462 --> 01:08:24,803
Inspector Lau.
Work with CIB to decode it.

630
01:08:25,468 --> 01:08:28,308
Find our man and get him out of there.
OK?

631
01:08:29,706 --> 01:08:31,726
And also...

632
01:08:32,108 --> 01:08:33,918
SP Wong was a good cop.

633
01:08:34,777 --> 01:08:38,407
We'll give him a hero's funeral.

634
01:08:38,982 --> 01:08:41,702
- OK?
- (all) Yes, sir.

635
01:08:49,892 --> 01:08:51,761
(phone rings)

636
01:08:54,930 --> 01:08:57,481
Boss, you went overboard this time.

637
01:08:58,734 --> 01:09:01,165
He was getting too close.
It was either him or me.

638
01:09:01,571 --> 01:09:04,611
I'm in charge here now. I can make
your next transaction go smoothly.

639
01:09:05,140 --> 01:09:09,120
No need. We got the goods
when they killed the cop today.

640
01:09:11,180 --> 01:09:13,870
A nice distraction, eh?

641
01:10:01,764 --> 01:10:02,934
(phone switches on)

642
01:10:04,267 --> 01:10:06,347
(phone rings)

643
01:10:08,571 --> 01:10:10,531
(phone rings)

644
01:10:21,250 --> 01:10:23,000
(snaps phone shut)

645
01:10:27,724 --> 01:10:30,124
(dials)

646
01:10:31,527 --> 01:10:33,427
(phone rings)

647
01:10:48,644 --> 01:10:51,454
(tapping of Morse code)

648
01:11:17,440 --> 01:11:18,900
(phone rings)

649
01:11:20,910 --> 01:11:23,080
(Yan) Why are you calling me?

650
01:11:24,981 --> 01:11:26,911
It's really you.

651
01:11:28,618 --> 01:11:31,658
- Who are you?
- Inspector Lau at OCTB.

652
01:11:37,226 --> 01:11:39,596
Maybe you should come home.

653
01:11:39,996 --> 01:11:42,166
l have unfinished business.

654
01:11:42,932 --> 01:11:45,922
SP Wong wouldn't want you
to take the law into your own hands.

655
01:11:46,402 --> 01:11:48,952
What do you want?

656
01:11:49,372 --> 01:11:51,422
Cooperation.

657
01:11:59,715 --> 01:12:02,265
(newsreader) Police have discovered
the body of a fugitive suspect

658
01:12:02,685 --> 01:12:07,255
involved in the Sheung Wan shootout
earlier today,

659
01:12:07,957 --> 01:12:11,997
and have confirmed the body
is that of undercover cop Keung.

660
01:12:12,628 --> 01:12:14,527
The OCTB have expressed
their condolences

661
01:12:14,864 --> 01:12:16,204
and have promised
a thorough investigation.

662
01:12:16,465 --> 01:12:17,425
Boss, Yan is back.

663
01:12:17,633 --> 01:12:20,443
Three vehicles collided
in Yuen Long today.

664
01:12:20,903 --> 01:12:24,303
One driver was trapped
until firefighters arrived.

665
01:12:27,510 --> 01:12:30,290
- Boss.
- Yan.

666
01:12:31,714 --> 01:12:34,464
I took care of Keung.

667
01:12:34,951 --> 01:12:37,001
Did he know about the warehouse?

668
01:12:38,187 --> 01:12:40,617
We could have problems if he did.

669
01:12:50,066 --> 01:12:51,146
(man) Boss.

670
01:12:51,367 --> 01:12:53,887
- We're still being followed.
- Keep circling around.

671
01:12:54,303 --> 01:12:57,233
(man) Spread the word.
Make sure the others know.

672
01:13:05,948 --> 01:13:07,818
Inspector Cheung.

673
01:13:09,085 --> 01:13:11,515
Tell our guys to drop the tail on Sam.

674
01:13:15,625 --> 01:13:18,025
He's headed to the warehouse,
but he'll change course

675
01:13:18,427 --> 01:13:20,536
if he thinks he's being tailed.

676
01:13:23,266 --> 01:13:25,545
Just call them off.
Do it for SP Wong if not for me.

677
01:13:25,935 --> 01:13:27,775
I need your help.

678
01:13:28,471 --> 01:13:30,781
Tell them!

679
01:13:31,173 --> 01:13:33,223
This isn't my case.

680
01:13:33,576 --> 01:13:36,156
I'm not getting involved.

681
01:13:36,579 --> 01:13:39,599
If you want something, talk to them.

682
01:13:40,683 --> 01:13:43,143
I know you blame me for SP Wong's death.

683
01:13:43,552 --> 01:13:46,482
But I'm a cop just like you.
And I want to solve this case!

684
01:13:47,590 --> 01:13:49,960
And get promoted too?

685
01:13:51,727 --> 01:13:53,277
I got a tip from Wong's mole.

686
01:13:53,562 --> 01:13:58,072
Don't you want the chance
to finish the job that SP Wong started?

687
01:13:59,702 --> 01:14:01,542
Huh?

688
01:14:36,205 --> 01:14:38,045
Update.

689
01:14:45,247 --> 01:14:49,287
Attention: target vehicle
on Highway Number Three.

690
01:14:57,560 --> 01:15:01,040
U-turn at Pier Number Three
to Lung Cheung Road.

691
01:15:13,142 --> 01:15:16,541
Targets arrived and are on their way
up to the car park,

692
01:15:35,965 --> 01:15:38,835
Hey, Lau. I'm not supposed
to be on this case.

693
01:15:39,301 --> 01:15:42,231
It's your ass if this thing crashes.

694
01:15:47,209 --> 01:15:50,398
They're loading up at 4P.
Elephant, stand by at exit 3P.

695
01:15:50,913 --> 01:15:54,723
Double 8, stand by at entrance 2P.
Fishball, Cheung, stand by here.

696
01:15:55,317 --> 01:15:57,867
- Everyone wait for my signal.
- (voices over radio) Yes, sir.

697
01:16:16,138 --> 01:16:18,948
Hey, Boss told me to stay behind.
Drop me here.

698
01:16:47,903 --> 01:16:49,803
- Go! Go!
- Police!

699
01:16:50,139 --> 01:16:52,329
(shouting)

700
01:17:05,421 --> 01:17:07,291
Run them over.

701
01:17:12,628 --> 01:17:15,148
(sirens)

702
01:17:27,409 --> 01:17:29,489
(phone rings, echoing)

703
01:17:49,965 --> 01:17:51,575
(ringing stops)

704
01:17:57,573 --> 01:17:59,353
My master always said...

705
01:17:59,675 --> 01:18:02,925
"What millions died
that Caesar might be great."

706
01:18:04,513 --> 01:18:07,823
But you can choose your own future.

707
01:18:08,350 --> 01:18:09,690
(gunshot)

708
01:18:14,023 --> 01:18:16,453
(body hits water)

709
01:18:22,231 --> 01:18:24,281
I've chosen.

710
01:19:01,136 --> 01:19:03,976
Here's some coffee.

711
01:19:10,646 --> 01:19:13,166
He's been waiting.

712
01:19:21,890 --> 01:19:23,790
So it's you?

713
01:19:28,397 --> 01:19:31,057
- How's the stereo?
- Pretty good.

714
01:19:31,533 --> 01:19:35,543
The tubes have to warm up.
After ten minutes they sound great.

715
01:19:36,205 --> 01:19:38,695
- Should I salute you?
- Forget it.

716
01:19:40,109 --> 01:19:42,069
How long have you been undercover?

717
01:19:42,411 --> 01:19:45,891
Been with Sam three years.
A few others before him.

718
01:19:46,448 --> 01:19:50,318
- Altogether, it's been ten years.
- Ten years? I should salute you instead.

719
01:19:50,919 --> 01:19:54,019
I just want my life back.
I want to be normal.

720
01:19:55,457 --> 01:19:57,797
Had enough?

721
01:19:58,193 --> 01:20:00,883
If you've never been a mole
you can't understand.

722
01:20:04,400 --> 01:20:08,710
Too bad I couldn't find Sam's mole.
I'd like to take him down.

723
01:20:14,510 --> 01:20:17,140
It's over now.
Let me give you back your identity.

724
01:20:18,080 --> 01:20:21,269
I'd open your file,
but no one knows the password.

725
01:20:23,252 --> 01:20:25,622
It's Morse code for "undercover."

726
01:20:26,955 --> 01:20:29,355
That's it?

727
01:21:14,436 --> 01:21:17,306
You're telling me
you can't spell "bodyguard"?

728
01:21:17,773 --> 01:21:20,933
- What, this isn't right?
- Not even close.

729
01:22:36,285 --> 01:22:38,125
DELETE

730
01:22:52,034 --> 01:22:54,643
EMPTY PROTECTED FILE

731
01:23:32,841 --> 01:23:34,831
Dr. Lee.

732
01:23:35,177 --> 01:23:38,607
- [didn't think you'd come.
- You're wanted by the police.

733
01:23:40,015 --> 01:23:41,885
It's not what it looks like.

734
01:23:42,251 --> 01:23:43,951
Let's talk upstairs.

735
01:23:47,623 --> 01:23:51,053
You told me you were a cop. Is that true?

736
01:23:51,994 --> 01:23:55,273
It's true. But I can't prove it.

737
01:24:00,636 --> 01:24:02,596
What's your plan?

738
01:24:02,938 --> 01:24:06,038
Don't have one. Still thinking.

739
01:24:19,888 --> 01:24:22,758
I just wanted to tell you something.

740
01:24:23,225 --> 01:24:26,325
Though it's embarrassing.

741
01:24:31,567 --> 01:24:34,027
Remember I said I dreamt about you?

742
01:24:34,436 --> 01:24:36,276
It's true.

743
01:24:43,879 --> 01:24:46,159
Me too.

744
01:25:29,224 --> 01:25:32,734
REMEMBER MY SECRET.
DON'T TELL ANYONE.

745
01:25:49,211 --> 01:25:51,141
Mary.

746
01:25:51,480 --> 01:25:54,230
What's the matter? Is it broken?

747
01:26:02,257 --> 01:26:04,507
(music)

748
01:26:04,926 --> 01:26:07,616
This morning, a guy from
the electronics store came by.

749
01:26:08,063 --> 01:26:09,843
He tuned it up.

750
01:26:11,733 --> 01:26:13,633
He left a CD for you.

751
01:26:15,270 --> 01:26:17,520
I listened to it.

752
01:26:22,978 --> 01:26:26,018
Have you eaten yet? I'll get you something.

753
01:26:27,449 --> 01:26:29,499
Iced tea?

754
01:26:29,851 --> 01:26:31,991
A snack?

755
01:26:32,354 --> 01:26:34,404
Sure.

756
01:26:49,204 --> 01:26:51,514
I can't finish my story.

757
01:26:55,744 --> 01:26:58,704
Unless I know if the lead is good or bad.

758
01:27:01,349 --> 01:27:04,949
He has to make up his mind.

759
01:27:05,620 --> 01:27:08,050
(on CD) I'm getting a shipment in.

760
01:27:08,457 --> 01:27:10,267
They're watching.

761
01:27:10,625 --> 01:27:12,705
Do what you need to do.

762
01:27:13,061 --> 01:27:15,340
But get this mole.

763
01:27:16,298 --> 01:27:18,728
! don't have access.
! can't arouse suspicion.

764
01:27:19,134 --> 01:27:21,854
So you're not worried about me,

765
01:27:22,304 --> 01:27:24,144
you're worried about yourself,
Inspector Lau.

766
01:27:28,944 --> 01:27:34,684
Voices crisp enough?
That recording was from Sam's office.

767
01:27:35,550 --> 01:27:37,280
There are plenty more like it.

768
01:27:37,586 --> 01:27:39,696
Don't threaten me. What do you want?

769
01:27:40,055 --> 01:27:42,105
l want my identity back.

770
01:27:42,457 --> 01:27:45,327
3pm, Central Ferry Pier. Keep your cell on.

771
01:28:08,650 --> 01:28:12,750
The number you have dialed can't be
connected, Please leave a message.

772
